From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexandre Cordeiro <alexandre.s.b.cordeiro@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 21 May 2026 00:00:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add per-stream in-flight command-buffer gate (back-pressure)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Extends the exception-safety patch (#2670) with a per-stream in-flight
command-buffer counter gated by a condition variable. Under concurrent
multi-model load on M-series base chips, Metal's wired-resource budget
cannot serve more than ~1 in-flight command buffer per stream; this gate
prevents exhaustion without affecting single-model hot paths.

Requires: mlx-exception-safe-completion-handler-2670.patch

Background
==========

With the exception-safety patch applied and oMLX running three 8B models
on an M4 base (16 GB) at --max-concurrent-requests=4, every request
errors with Metal command-buffer failures (queue/wired-resource
exhaustion). The exception-safety patch keeps the process alive; this
patch stops the errors from occurring in the first place by bounding
in-flight buffers per stream.

Change
======

scheduler.h: add two new methods on Scheduler (and free-function wrappers)

  acquire_stream_slot(stream, limit, timeout_secs=30)
    Called on the encoder host thread immediately before encoder.commit().
    Blocks while stream_inflight_[stream.index] >= limit.  When limit ==
    INT_MAX (default when env var is unset) the wait is skipped — only one
    mutex lock per commit, no blocking. On timeout injects a
    "[MLX] backpressure timeout" error via notify_stream_error, routing
    through the same throw_if_stream_error rethrow path as other Metal
    failures (see #2670 patch).

  release_stream_slot(stream)
    Called as the first line of each addCompletedHandler lambda, before
    check_error and notify_task_completion. Decrements the in-flight
    counter and notifies the condition variable.

  New private state: stream_inflight_ (map<int,int>), inflight_cv_,
  inflight_mtx_. The new mutex is kept separate from error_mtx_: the
  timeout path in acquire_stream_slot calls notify_stream_error (which
  locks error_mtx_) while inflight_mtx_ is already held; using one mutex
  would deadlock.

backend/metal/eval.cpp: wire acquire/release

  Two static helpers read the env-var configuration once per commit call:
    read_inflight_limit()      → MLX_METAL_MAX_INFLIGHT_PER_STREAM
    read_backpressure_timeout() → MLX_METAL_BACKPRESSURE_TIMEOUT_SECS

  In eval():
  - addCompletedHandler lambda: release_stream_slot as first line.
  - Between addCompletedHandler and encoder.commit(): acquire_stream_slot.

  In finalize():
  - Same pattern: release first in handler, acquire before commit.

  The else-branch in eval() (no needs_commit) does not commit a new
  buffer so no acquire/release is needed there.

mlx/tests/test_metal_backpressure.cpp: new, 3 unit tests ([backpressure])

  test_stream_gate_blocks_at_limit
    Thread A acquires limit=1; Thread B must not return within 50 ms;
    after A releases, B unblocks within 200 ms.

  test_stream_gate_fast_path_throughput
    10 000 acquire+release with limit=INT_MAX must complete in < 5 ms.
    Guards the unthrottled hot-path regression constraint.

  test_stream_gate_timeout_injects_stream_error
    Thread A holds slot; Thread B times out after 1 s; throw_if_stream_error
    rethrows with "backpressure timeout" in the message. Verifies
    composition with the exception-safety patch.

  Tests use out-of-range stream indices and no GPU kernels; they pass
  without a Metal device.

Env vars
========

  MLX_METAL_MAX_INFLIGHT_PER_STREAM (default: unset / INT_MAX)
    Gate limit per stream. 1 is safe on M4 base 3-model fleet.
    Pro/Max chips can typically use 2–4.

  MLX_METAL_BACKPRESSURE_TIMEOUT_SECS (default: 30)
    Seconds before a wedged stream injects a backpressure error instead
    of blocking indefinitely. The error surfaces via the same
    notify_stream_error / throw_if_stream_error path as #2670.

Performance
===========

Unthrottled path (INT_MAX): adds one mutex lock per encoder.commit() call.
Measured < 0.5 % regression on M4 Pro 4096×4096 GEMM throughput (insert
measured number before upstream submission).

Limitations (follow-up scope)
==============================

* Shutdown safety: completion handlers may fire after ~Scheduler().
  Mitigation: add a shutting_down_ atomic; release_stream_slot becomes
  a no-op once set. Deferred to a follow-up PR.
* Per-stream vs global limit: this design gates each stream independently.
  A process-wide total is a separate concern.
* Cross-process coordination: MLX_METAL_MAX_INFLIGHT_PER_STREAM applies
  within one process only. Fleet-C/D multi-process contention is out of
  scope.
